    dc:date "2020" ;
    dc:title "Disentangling vines: a study of morphological crypsis and genetic divergence in vine snakes (Squamata: Colubridae: Ahaetulla) with the description of five new species from Peninsular India" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4423520>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4423551>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4423530>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4423524>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4423553> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4423520>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. PCA plot shows quantitative morphological space shared by Western Ghats Ahaetulla spp.. In the figure, members of the Ahaetulla nasuta species complex with lineages L3—A. borealis sp. nov. (dark blue crosses), L4—A. farnsworthi sp. nov. (green filled squares), L5—A. isabellina comb. nov. (brown cross) and L6—A. malabarica sp. nov. (black squares) from the Western Ghats are clustered together and share morphological space. The PCA plots correspond to the scores and loadings presented in Appendix IV (D, E & F)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4423520/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4423551>
    dc:description "FIGURE 13. Images of Ahaetulla isabellina comb. nov. Images of holotype BNHS 3584 (CESS183). (a) Head lateral, (b) Head Dorsal, (c) Ventral section, (d–f) Dissected hemipenis, (g) Whole specimen. Images of live individuals, (h) BNHS 3584 (CESS183) head lateral, (i) head lateral of CESS182, (j) body section of CESS182. Image of a live, uncollected individual from Valparai, (k) showing threat display (Images a & b; d, e & f to scale, other images not to scale)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4423551/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4423530>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Ahaetulla lineages in Peninsular India and Sri Lanka showing side-by-side comparison of their superficial head morphology and maxillary dentition. (From the top) (a) Ahaetulla farnsworthi sp. nov. (b) A. isabellina comb. nov. (c) A. malabarica sp. nov. (d) A. borealis sp. nov. (e) A. nasuta (f) A. oxyrhyncha comb. nov. (g) A. sahyadrensis nom. nov. (h) A. travancorica sp. nov. (i) A. dispar & A. travancorica sp. nov. (j) A. perroteti (1) Ahaetulla farnsworthi sp. nov. (2) A. isabellina comb. nov. (3) A. malabarica sp. nov. (4) A. borealis sp. nov. (5) A. nasuta (6) A. oxyrhyncha comb. nov. (7) A. pulverulenta (8) A. sahyadrensis nom. nov. (9) A. dispar (10) A. travancorica sp. nov. (11) A. perroteti." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4423530/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4423524>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Maps showing the distribution of lineages in the Western Ghats (in Peninsular India) and Sri Lanka. (A) Map showing our study’s point locations of Ahaetulla farnsworthi sp. nov., A. isabellina comb. nov., A. malabarica sp. nov., A. borealis sp. nov., A. nasuta & A. oxyrhyncha comb. nov.. (B) Map showing our study’s point locations of Ahaetulla perroteti, A. dispar & A. travancorica sp. nov.." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4423524/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4423553>
    dc:description "FIGURE 14. Habitat of Ahaetulla isabellina comb. nov., near Valparai, Anamalai Hills, Southern Western Ghats (Tirupur district, Tamil Nadu State, India) showing evergreen and semi-evergreen forest vegetation types." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4423553/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

